The Social Democratic Party governorship candidate in Ogun State, Engr Tony Ojeshina, has stepped down for his Peopleâ€™s Democratic Party (PDP) rival, Ladi Adebutu, ahead of the March 18 election. Ojeshina, a former commissioner in the state, announced this at a press conference in Abeokuta on Thursday. He was flanked by his running mate, Aare Gbenga Oluyemi and the Deputy Chairman, Aare Sola Coker. He, however, said all the State House of Assembly candidates of the party were still in the race for the March 18 election.